{
  "texts": [
    "• Conducting the first comprehensive evaluation of these three SSL categories together in the wearable HAR domain, considering both data-rich and data-scarce environments.",
    "• The study is fully reproducible since all research results, code, and pre-trained models have been made publicly available on a repository for easy access and further exploration 1.",
    "• The findings indicate that MAE emerges as the most robust technique for the domain, surpassing all other approaches, including supervised pre-training methods.The paper is organized as follows.",
    "First, some background is provided about HAR and SSL techniques.",
    "Next, we detail the process of obtaining multiple pre-trained models using adapted SSL techniques with two different network architectures."
  ]
}